init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The world is now controlled by the United Nations, and the U.S. is the only country that is not a member.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They had the best technology and the best of everything.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The US was in a state of shock and disbelief.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They had no idea what to do.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The US was in a state of panic.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They had to do something, but what?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They decided to go to the moon to see if they could find any clues of what China had done to get ahead of them.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They came up with a rocket that would get them to the moon in less than 12 hours.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They had to go to China to get the parts, but they had to get permission from the UN to do so.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The US went to the UN and asked for permission to go to China to get the parts to upgrade their current system.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They were not going to let the UN stop them from getting to the moon.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They were going to get those parts no matter what.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They went to China and got the parts.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They were able to upgrade their system and get to the moon in less than 12 hours.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The US was now on the moon and they were looking for clues of what China had done to get ahead of them.
